  "body": "Why when I'm trying to use some async function as an event handler I don't get Component context?\r\n\r\nFor example, It's a handler for Select:\r\n```\r\nhandlerChangeSomeFilter = async ({ target: { name, value } }) => {\r\n    const { filters } = this.state // context is different here \r\n}\r\n```\r\nWhat are the ways? I use not nice the way.\r\n```\r\nhandlerChangeSomeFilter = () => async ({ target: { name, value } }) => {\r\n    const { filters } = this.state // context is different here \r\n}\r\n\r\n......\r\n\r\n<select onChange={this.handlerChangeSomeFilter()}}/>\r\n```\r\n",
